        <section name="Introduction">
            <table>
                <tr>
                    <th>Force Field X Modules</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <p>
                            Force Field X is a collaboration to develop computational tools
                            for molecular biophysics, including state-of-the-art features for X-ray
                            crystallography and drug design. Force Field X modules include:
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><a href="modules/algorithms/index.html">Algorithms</a> for optimization and sampling.</li>
                            <li><a href="modules/binding/index.html">Binding Affinity</a> for computing binding affinities.</li>
                            <li><a href="modules/crystal/index.html">Crystal</a> for spacegroup symmetry operations.</li>
                            <li><a href="modules/numerics/index.html">Numerics</a> for numerical methods.</li>
                            <li><a href="modules/potential/index.html">Potentials</a> for computing the potential energy of the system.</li>
                            <li><a href="modules/ui/index.html">User Interfaces</a> for command line and GUI versions.</li>
                            <li><a href="modules/utilities/index.html">Utilities</a> for support functions needed by many modules.</li>
                            <li><a href="modules/xray/index.html">X-Ray Refinement</a> for refinement of X-ray diffraction data sets.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </td>
